---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Button from "@components/Button.astro";
const title = 'When to Call Me';
const description = 'Concrete decision triggers and a bounded next step for requesting an independent architectural verdict on SAP BTP.';
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  <section class="stack tight">
    <h1>When to call me</h1>
    <p class="measure">Use this page to decide whether the issue should stop being internally absorbed. If the decision no longer converges, move to a fixed‑scope review.</p>
  </section>

  <h2>Decision triggers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No team can legitimately approve the next change end‑to‑end.</li>
    <li>Work continues; the decision does not converge.</li>
    <li>Teams are locally correct; the system remains globally unstable.</li>
    <li>Rollout or hardening exposes assumptions that should have been settled earlier.</li>
    <li>Works in Postman; fails behind App Router or Work Zone.</li>
    <li>Tenant variance appears during onboarding or expansion.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why continuing internally may feel safer — and still increase risk</h2>
  <p class="measure">Familiar delivery motions lower friction, not risk. When the failure is jurisdiction across boundaries, more implementation entrenches the wrong contract and delays the decision.</p>

  <h2>What you probably do not need me for</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Staffing on implementation or delivery tickets.</li>
    <li>Low‑level troubleshooting with clear ownership already established.</li>
    <li>Generic advisory without a concrete architectural decision to make.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What to send</h2>
  <p class="measure">Send one structured page:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Landscape — S/4, BTP runtimes, entry surfaces, identity</li>
    <li>Divergence — what works where; what fails where</li>
    <li>Timeline — go‑live, rollout, recent changes</li>
    <li>Ownership — who holds what today</li>
    <li>Decision — the choice that cannot converge</li>
  </ol>
  <div style="display:flex; gap:.75rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <Button href="mailto:pei_jiandong@hotmail.com" variant="primary">Send structured summary</Button>
    <Button href="/work/" variant="ghost">See engagement formats</Button>
  </div>

  <h2>What happens next</h2>
  <p class="measure">I confirm whether the situation matches a boundary failure pattern. If appropriate, we proceed with a fixed‑scope triage, audit, or verdict — defined in writing, time‑bounded, and outcome‑specific. Where executive‑level convergence is required, the Executive Boundary Verdict defines final jurisdiction. No sales funnel.</p>

  <p>For the model behind this assessment, see the <a href="/boundary-model/">Boundary Model</a>. For essays, see <a href="/insights/">Insights</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
